G-Force Steam - Urban and Building Cleaning Specialists

G-Force Steam are experts in cleaning all types of building exteriors and large surface areas.
With offices based in the Midlands and Wales, we cover the whole of the UK.

Our portfolio ranges from major public buildings, historic houses and
heritage sites to sports stadiums, shopping centres, offices, factories and forecourts.

We've cleaned Birmingham Symphony Hall, Birmingham Repertory Theatre and the National Indoor Arena.
We've worked on the International Convention Centre, the spectacular Barclaycard Arena and the FA's National Football Centre.

We've revived listed buildings and monuments, including the listed St Georges Park former hospital in Stafford and the historic granary
building at Weston Park, The National War Memorial Arboretum. We've even cleaned the deck of the famous Iron Bridge of Shropshire.

Our Services

First impressions are important! If years of accumulated dirt and grime on the walls of your company building is projecting the wrong image of your business, then it's time to call in G-Force Steam. And if the surrounding grounds have seen better days, we can transform those too. G-Force Steam also specialise in large surface area cleaning including pavements, precincts, car parks and garage forecourts

Restorative cleaning transforms a building or paved surface area to its original appearance, removing decades of dirt and pollution. It adds value, reduces maintenance costs and improves the lifespan of a building. Long-term durability can be extended through the addition of a high quality, breathable, surface protection sealant that repels staining and damage from the elements.
